column4: For each of the statements below, how often do you feel this way about your job?
column22: To what extent do you agree or disagree with the following statements about your job?
column46: To what extent do you agree or disagree with the following statements about your work?

column1: This sheet contains questions relating to: job design and work pressure, and being respected and valued at work
column4: a) I look forward to going to work
column10: b) I am enthusiastic about my job
column16: c) Time passes quickly when I am working
column22: a) I have clear, planned goals and objectives for my job
column28: b) I always know what my work responsibilities are
column34: c) I am trusted to do my job
column40: d) I am able to do my job to a standard I am personally pleased with
column46: a) There are frequent opportunities for me to show initiative in my role
column52: b) I am able to make suggestions to improve the work of my team / department
column58: c) I am involved in deciding on changes introduced that affect my work area / team / department
column64: d) I am able to make improvements happen in my area of work
column70: e) I am unable to meet all the conflicting demands on my time at work
column76: f) I have adequate materials, supplies and equipment to do my work
column82: g) There are enough staff at this organisation for me to do my job properly
